# Verification Expectations

After substantive edits, run the narrowest relevant check and broaden based on risk.

- `.nf` or `.config`: affected module/workflow stub-run with `-profile test -stub-run`.
- Shell scripts: `shellcheck -S warning` on the CI glob in `goodworkflows-verify` if available; otherwise `bash -n`.
- Docs: docs generation and `mkdocs build --strict` when docs tooling or rendered docs changed.
- Python tests under `tests/`: run the relevant pytest selection when Python tooling is available.
- Template changes: combine syntax review with affected stub-run, because rendered `.command.sh` can differ from source.

If a check cannot run locally, say which tool or data was missing.
